//! Specialized memory allocators and layout utilities.
//!
//! This module re-exports allocator types from `core` under a unified
//! namespace. The canonical definitions live in `core::arena`, `core::pool`,
//! `core::cache`, and `core::soo`.
//!
//! # Modules
//!
//! | Module | Description | Canonical |
//! |--------|-------------|-----------|
//! | [`arena`] | Bump-pointer arena allocator | `core::arena` |
//! | [`pool`] | Lock-free object pool | `core::pool` |
//! | [`cache`] | Cache-line aligned storage | `core::cache` |
//! | [`soo`] | Small object optimization | `core::soo` |
//!
//! # When to Use
//!
//! - **Arena**: Many small, short-lived allocations freed together (parsers, ASTs)
//! - **Pool**: Reuse objects to avoid allocation overhead (connection pools, buffers)
//! - **Cache**: Performance-critical data that must avoid false sharing
//! - **SOO**: Small collections that usually fit inline (< 8 elements)

pub mod arena
pub mod pool
pub mod cache
pub mod soo
